This paper deals with the performance of multimedia transmission in cognitive radio systems, which involves the use of information theory (cs.IT) for hierarchical modulation-based transmission and channel sensing (cs.NI) for interference management. The focus on multimedia transmission (cs.MM) and cognitive radio (cs.CR) further supports these categories. Additionally, the paper discusses power control strategies (cs.COM) to optimize the transmission performance.
